NAME: {{package}}

AUTHOR:

DESCRIPTION:

Describe your application here.

{{package}} is built on the Cement CLI Application Framework.


USAGE:

    $ {{package}} --help
    
    
PLUGIN DEVELOPMENT:

{{package}} supports external plugins via the Cement Framework.  To quick
start a new plugin for {{package}} you can use the paster utility.

Setup a virtual environment for development:
    
    $ virtualenv --no-site-package /path/to/env
    
    $ source /path/to/env/bin/activate
    
    
Install {{package}}:
    
    $ cd /path/to/{{package}}
    
    $ python setup.py develop
    

Create and install the plugin:

    $ mkdir plugins
    
    $ cd plugins
    
    $ paster cement-plugin {{package}} myplugin
    
    $ cd {{package}}-plugins-myplugin
    
    $ python setup.py develop
    
    
Once your plugin is installed, you can add the plugin to the enabled_plugins
setting in /etc/{{package}}/{{package}}.conf.  Additionally, the plugin
configurations can be set in /etc/{{package}}/plugins.d/myplugin.conf. You 
should then see some example commands/options show up with:

    $ {{package}} --help
    
    
Then, code away!
